{
  "text": "Previous studies have shown that i-SCAN was able to better detect flat or \"nonprotruding\" lesions and small polyps; however, this study did not show increased detection of flat adenomas [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The contradictory findings could be explained by some of our reported polyps only having a qualitative size descriptor of \"diminutive\" without further clarification of flat/sessile shape. Lack of a formally standardized definition of \"flat\" polyp could also explain our discordant findings. Our findings do concur with increased detection of \"small\" adenomas although the defined sizes for \"small\" in the study by Testoni were <10 mm and ours were <6 mm [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "8356415",
    "[CITATION_2]": "40207303",
    "[CITATION_3]": "40207303"
